Method Detail

min

public T min()
This method returns the smallest element or null if the heap is empty. It does not change the heap so two successive calls two min will return the same element.

Note: Its worst-case runtime is O(1).

Specified by:
min in interface PriorityQueue<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
Returns:
the smallest element or null if empty
See Also:
PriorityQueue.extractMin(), PriorityQueue.decreaseKey(de.raulin.rosario.heaps.PQNode)

extractMin

public T extractMin()
Returns the smallest element or null if the heap is empty. It consolidates the heap so that the next call to extractMin returns the second smallest element (or null if the heap is empty).

Note: Its amortized runtime is O(log(n)).

Specified by:
extractMin in interface PriorityQueue<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
Returns:
the smallest element or null if empty

decreaseKey

public void decreaseKey(PQNode<T> element)
Rearranges the queue after element's priority decreased.

Note: This method does not work if element's priority increased! Its amortized runtime is O(1).
